social_posts.post_text: I only posted 3 pictures on this app last year and I want to double it this year so I’m starting now 💪 Happy new year my beautiful IG followers, I’ll probably just continue putting pics of steak in my stories but I appreciate you being along for the ride!

It’s the first of the month so I am posting pictures from the previous month, per Instagram’s rules. Except for the first picture, which is a picture from today. Please like this picture to fuel me for another month. 1 like = 1 alive. #Instagram #Influencer #Travel #Sports

I had to move out of my apartment on a day’s notice and @RoadwayMoving came through in the clutch. The great movers had me packed and into my new place in no time at all.

If you’re moving you can get a sweet deal with them! Use code BARSTOOLNATE10 for $$$ off your next move. #roadwaymoving #movewithroadway

Another first of the month, another Instagram post from me. I ended up doing 2 posts last month, which means I will be doing 3 posts this month. That’s right, 3 times you can give me that sweet, sweet dopamine fuel by clicking like on the pictures I put up. As they say, what’s even the point of living if people don’t like your Instagram pictures. So please, give me that rush of blood to the head. #Influencer #Sports #ForYou

I was lucky enough to play my first ever streamed poker game on @hustlercasinolive which also was the highest stakes I’ve ever played. It started out fun, getting a bluff with 72o through, but later on I played a hand pretty terribly vs @missbotez and ended up losing for the night. Overall it was a great experience and can’t wait to do it again, hopefully with better results. Had a blast though playing with the future of poker @brycehall @tommyunold @nickaustin @joshrichards @hoodieallen @missbotez 
Thank you @hustlercasinolive for having us!

I promised 3 Instagram posts this month and by golly I have delivered. You can see I did many memorable things this month, like drink coffee and take a picture of myself (commonly known as a “selfie”) in front of the Pacific Ocean before getting food poisoning from a batch of bad oysters. March was definitely a month. Don’t forget to like this post so I can sleep soundly at night. 1 like = 1 I hate puppy cancer. I will be back for 4 posts in April. Xoxo.

An assortment of pictures from the last couple of months. I failed on my quest to post more on this app, I instead mostly just post pictures of bagels and the Titanic on my story. But I also saw blink 182 and went to Vegas (and broke my foot but I never talk about it) so I decided to post some of those so when I lose my memory in 3-4 years I can look back and try to remember like the old lady in the Notebook. Don’t forget to like the post because as we all know self-worth and value is solely based on getting attention on social media and I have a few months to make up for. Namaste.
We bought @barstoolsports back today. Proud of us @stoolpresidente

Nice August so far. Bought back Barstool, put on two shoes for the first time since May, and hung with friends. That’s pretty much it. Don’t have some long caption for this one like posts of the past. Just short and to the point. Good vibes only for the rest of the year. And yes, @marcroberge did hop into the crowd, hang for a bit, and then go back on stage. Legend.
Took ☝️ picture at the Barstool 20th Anniversary show. 🚀🐶
Took this picture and thought it turned out really nicely (no filter obv) so thought I’d share it on the grid for all to see! #NYC
The best sweater we’ve ever made is onsale now in the @barstoolstore. But first, who did the best WHERE ARE YEWWWWWW @tomdelonge
Tonight! My reality show career begins on Surviving Barstool. Also yes I look fantastic. Watch!!!

My 2023 New Year’s resolution was to post more pics on IG and I didn’t do that at all. So here’s some pictures from the last few months that I like. Maybe next year I’ll become a better influencer, we’ll see. Thinking about getting into really good shape. Anyway, 1 like=1 influence. Blessings to all.
